  "summary": "While rowing on the lake, Anthony Kidd questions Bandel regarding her French tutor, Jeanne Viel. Bandel explains that she hired Viel through an agency for a hundred pounds a year and notes that Viel previously lived for ten years at the Chateau de Briodulle in Digne, France, in the house of the Comtesse de Briodulle. Anthony observes that Bandel has only ever corresponded with the Countess by letter and has never met her in person.\n\nDuring their conversation, Bandel mentions that while Chimney House has historical significance, it is frequently used for tourist tours led by Mr. Tredwell. Anthony notices a melancholy man named Bill by the boathouse, and after Bandel goes to meet him, Anthony plays a game with two children, Giggles and Shimmer. Following the game, Anthony spots a black-bearded stranger hurrying across the courtyard and subsequently encounters a flushed, out-of-breath Mr. Fitch.\n\nAfter Chief Constable Bartle appears, Anthony requests permission from Sheriff Balthazar to travel to the Chateau de Briodulle in Digne, France. Anthony plans to depart following tomorrow's autopsy and intends to return by Sunday evening. The Sheriff grants permission on the condition that Anthony returns directly. Anthony expresses his suspicion that a specific memoir is the central cause of the ongoing troubles at the estate.",
